00214 /*! Full frames are always delivered reliably */
00215 struct ast_iax2_full_hdr {
00216    unsigned short scallno; /*!< Source call number -- high bit must be 1 */
00217    unsigned short dcallno; /*!< Destination call number -- high bit is 1 if retransmission */
00218    unsigned int ts;     /*!< 32-bit timestamp in milliseconds (from 1st transmission) */
00219    unsigned char oseqno;   /*!< Packet number (outgoing) */
00220    unsigned char iseqno;   /*!< Packet number (next incoming expected) */
00221    unsigned char type;     /*!< Frame type */
00222    unsigned char csub;     /*!< Compressed subclass */
00223    unsigned char iedata[0];
00224 } __attribute__ ((__packed__));
00225 
00226 /*! Full frames are always delivered reliably */
00227 struct ast_iax2_full_enc_hdr {
00228    unsigned short scallno; /*!< Source call number -- high bit must be 1 */
00229    unsigned short dcallno; /*!< Destination call number -- high bit is 1 if retransmission */
00230    unsigned char encdata[0];

00233 /*! Mini header is used only for voice frames -- delivered unreliably */
00234 struct ast_iax2_mini_hdr {
00235    unsigned short callno;  /*!< Source call number -- high bit must be 0, rest must be non-zero */
00236    unsigned short ts;      /*!< 16-bit Timestamp (high 16 bits from last ast_iax2_full_hdr) */
00237                      /* Frametype implicitly VOICE_FRAME */
00238                      /* subclass implicit from last ast_iax2_full_hdr */
00239    unsigned char data[0];
00240 } __attribute__ ((__packed__));
